parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake calipers can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brakes extend to the floor
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the brakes overheat
a burning smell is present in the braking area
the ABS light stays on
the brakes bind on the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rotors can cause the brakes to overheat and fail, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brakes continuously overheat with normal use
the rotors crack and stick
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle.

symptoms: The ABS light stays on
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the brakes overheat
a burning smell is present in the braking area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's tendency to sway from right to left can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to rollover, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle sways or wanders from right to left while driving
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the vehicle feels unstable or unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Poor Quality and Reliability of RV Coach
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The numerous defects and failures in the RV coach can lead to safety hazards, discomfort, and inconvenience for the occupants, and may even render the vehicle unusable.
symptoms: Broken cabinets
plumbing leaks
electrical issues
and a growing list of problems with each use.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Customer Service and Repair Experience
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of effective communication, delayed repair timelines, and incomplete or ineffective repairs can lead to frustration, wasted time, and continued safety risks for the occupants.

delayed or back-ordered parts
